'''Adrenoleukodystrophy''' is a [[disease]] that is linked on the X [[chromosome]]. It is a result of [[fatty acid]] [[digestive system|digestive]] [[enzyme]]s not breaking up the [[fat]]s. These fats build up in the [[brain]]. They damage the [[myelin]] that surrounds [[nerve]]s. This can cause [[seizure]]s and [[hyperactivity]]. It can also cause problems with [[speech|speaking]], [[hearing|listening]] and understanding [[verbal]] [[wikt:instruction|instruction]]s.


